recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f.', 'In a large bowl, cream together butter and sugars.', 'Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.', 'In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.', 'Add dry ingredients to the wet ingredients and mix well.', 'Stir in chocolate chips.', 'Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.', 'Bake for 8-10 minutes.']

title: Peanut butter ice cream
recipe: ['In a large bowl, whisk together the peanut butter, sugar, egg yolks, milk and vanilla.', 'Pour into a large freezer safe bowl and freeze for at least 4 hours.', 'When ready to serve, remove the bowl from the freezer and whisk in the heavy cream.', 'Return the bowl to the freezer and freeze for about 1 hour.', 'Remove the bowl from the freezer and whisk again until smooth.', 'Return the mixture to the freezer and freeze for about 1 hour.', 'Remove the bowl from the freezer and whisk again until smooth.', 'Return the mixture to the freezer and freeze for about 1 hour.', 'Transfer the mixture to a food processor and pulse until smooth.', 'Return the mixture to the freezer and freeze']

title: Crostata di marmellata
recipe: ['In a food processor, pulse the flour, sugar and salt.', 'Add the butter and pulse until the mixture resembles coarse meal.', 'Add the ice water and pulse until the dough comes together.', 'Wrap the dough in plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.', 'Preheat the oven to 375.', 'On a lightly floured surface, roll out the dough to a 12-inch round.', 'Transfer the dough to a lightly floured work surface and cut into 8 wedges.', 'Transfer the wedges to a baking sheet and prick the dough all over with a fork.', 'Bake for about 15 minutes, until the edges are golden.', 'Let cool on the baking sheet for 10 minutes.', 'Serve warm or at room temperature.']

title: Blueberry cheesecake
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f (175 degrees c).', 'In a medium bowl, mix together graham cracker crumbs, sugar, and cinnamon.', 'Stir in melted butter until well blended.', 'Press into the bottom of a 9-inch springform pan.', 'Bake in preheated oven for 10 minutes.', 'Remove from oven and allow to cool.', 'In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.', 'Beat in sugar and vanilla until smooth.', 'Fold in blueberries.', 'Pour filling into crust.', 'Bake in preheated oven for 45 minutes, or until center is set.', 'Cool in pan for 10 minutes before removing to a wire rack to cool completely.', 'Refrigerate until serving.']

title: Chocolate shortbread
recipe: ['Heat oven to 350f.', 'Beat cream cheese, butter and vanilla in large bowl with mixer until blended.', 'Gradually beat in flour.', 'Stir in chocolate.', 'Press onto bottom of 9-inch springform pan sprayed with cooking spray.', 'Bake 20 min.', 'Or until lightly browned.', 'Cool completely.', 'Refrigerate 1 hour.', 'Use parchment handles to lift cheesecake from pan before cutting into wedges.']

title: Peanut butter cupcakes
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f (175 degrees c).', 'Line 24 muffin cups with paper liners.', 'Whisk flour, baking powder, and salt together in a bowl.', 'Beat peanut butter, vegetable oil, white sugar, brown sugar, and white sugar together in a separate bowl until smooth.', 'Beat eggs into peanut butter mixture until smooth.', 'Stir milk, vanilla extract, and flour mixture into peanut butter mixture until batter is just combined; fold in peanut butter.', 'Fill prepared muffin cups 2/3-full with batter.', 'Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center of a cupcake comes out clean, 20 to 25 minutes.']

title: Easy apple crisp
recipe: ['Heat oven to 375f.', 'Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon in large bowl.', 'Cut in butter with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.', 'Stir in egg.', 'Press onto bottom of 9-inch square baking dish sprayed with cooking spray.', 'Bake 20 min.', 'Or until lightly browned.', 'Meanwhile, mix apples and sugar in medium bowl.', 'Stir in flour mixture.', 'Spoon over hot crust.', 'Bake 25 to 30 min.', 'Or until apples are tender.']

title: Blueberry buckle
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f.', 'In a large bowl, cream together butter and sugar.', 'Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.', 'Stir in vanilla.', 'In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, and salt.', 'Add flour mixture to butter mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.', 'Fold in blueberries.', 'Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan.', 'Sprinkle with cinnamon.', 'Bake for 45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.', 'Cool on a wire rack.']

title: Memphis style ribs
recipe: ['Mix all ingredients except ribs in a large bowl.', 'Add ribs and toss to coat.', 'Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.', 'Preheat oven to 300 degrees.', 'Line a baking sheet with foil.', 'Place ribs on the prepared baking sheet.', 'Bake for 1 hour.', 'Remove ribs from oven and brush with the sauce.', 'Return ribs to oven and bake for 1 hour.']

title: Roasted red pepper and sea salt
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 400 degrees f. line a baking sheet with parchment paper.', 'Place peppers on baking sheet and drizzle with olive oil.', 'Sprinkle with sea salt.', 'Roast for 3040 minutes, until peppers are soft and caramelized.', 'Remove from oven and let cool.', 'Once cooled, peel and seed peppers.', 'Place peppers in a food processor and pulse until smooth.', 'Add sugar and pulse until combined.']

title: Roasted garlic and paprika roasted red pepper
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 400 degrees f (200 degrees c).', 'Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil.', 'Toss the roasted red peppers with olive oil, garlic powder, paprika, salt, and black pepper in a bowl.', 'Spread the peppers onto the prepared baking sheet.', 'Roast in the preheated oven until the skins are blackened and blistered, about 20 minutes.']

title: Kung pao chicken
recipe: ['Heat oil in large nonstick skillet on medium-high heat.', 'Add chicken; cook and stir 5 min.', 'Or until done.', 'Add next 4 ingredients; cook and stir 5 min.', 'Or until vegetables are crisp-tender.', 'Stir in soy sauce and chili powder; cook 1 min.', 'Or until heated through, stirring occasionally.', 'Sprinkle with cilantro.']

title: Creamy mashed potatoes
recipe: ['Place potatoes in large saucepan.', 'Add water; cover.', 'Bring to boil on medium-high heat.', 'Reduce heat to medium-low; simmer 15 min.', 'Or until potatoes are tender.', 'Drain potatoes; return to pan.', 'Add butter, milk and seasonings; mash until smooth.']

title: Apple pie
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 425 degrees f (220 degrees c).', 'In a large bowl, mix together the flour, sugar, salt, and nutmeg.', 'Cut in the butter until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.', 'Stir in the egg yolk and mix until the dough forms a ball.', 'Divide the dough into two pieces and roll each piece into a ball.', 'Place the dough balls onto a lightly floured surface and roll out to a 12-inch circle.', 'Place the dough circles onto a baking sheet.', 'Brush the dough circles with the egg white and sprinkle with the cinnamon sugar.', 'Bake in the preheated oven for 10 minutes, or until the crust is golden brown.']

title: Blueberry sorbet
recipe: ['In a medium saucepan, combine the blueberries, sugar and water.', 'Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.', 'Reduce the heat and simmer for 5 minutes.', 'Remove from the heat and let cool.', 'In a blender, puree the blueberries with the lemon juice and the sugar syrup.', 'Pour the mixture into a bowl and freeze for 2 hours.', 'Transfer the mixture to a food processor and puree until smooth.', 'Return to the freezer and freeze for 2 hours.', 'Scrape the mixture into a freezer-safe container and return to the freezer for 1 hour.']

title: Pineapple and cherry ice cream
recipe: ['In a medium bowl, combine the pineapple, cherries, sugar and lemon juice.', 'Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.', 'In a medium bowl, whisk together the milk and cream.', 'Pour the milk mixture into the bowl of ice cream maker and follow the manufacturers instructions.', 'When the ice cream is ready, pour it into a large bowl and stir in the pineapple mixture.', 'Cover and freeze for at least 4 hours or overnight.', 'Serve in bowls and garnish with maraschino cherries.']

title: Crunchy asian salad
recipe: ['Combine all ingredients except dressing in large bowl.', 'Add dressing; toss to coat.']

title: Kale and tomato soup

title: Roasted red pepper and sea salt
recipe: ['Preheat the oven to 400.', 'In a large bowl, toss the peppers with the olive oil and season with salt.', 'Spread the peppers on a baking sheet and roast for about 25 minutes, until tender and lightly browned.', 'Let cool.', 'Transfer the peppers to a food processor and puree until smooth.', 'Transfer the roasted peppers to a bowl and stir in the sugar.']

title: Easy caramel sauce
recipe: ['In a medium saucepan, combine the sugar, butter and water.', 'Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the sugar dissolves.', 'Increase the heat to medium-high and boil for 5 minutes.', 'Remove from the heat and stir in the caramel sauce.']

title: Roasted red potatoes
recipe: ['Heat oven to 450 degrees f.', 'Toss potatoes with dressing; spread onto bottom of 15x10x1-inch pan sprayed with cooking spray.', 'Bake 1 hour or until potatoes are tender, stirring after 30 min.', 'Sprinkle with cheese; bake 5 min.', 'Or until melted.']

title: Vanilla cookies

title: Orange & lime sangria

title: Raisin salad
recipe: ['Combine raisins and sugar in a bowl.', 'Add enough water to cover raisins by 1 inch.', 'Let stand 30 minutes.', 'Drain raisins and add to raisin mixture.', 'Stir in salt.']

title: Bbq pork chops

title: Slow-cooker shredded beef

title: Cinnamon onion bread
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f (175 degrees c).', 'Lightly grease a 9x13 inch baking dish.', 'In a medium bowl, mix together the cinnamon and sugar.', 'Place the bread slices in the prepared baking dish.', 'Sprinkle with the onion and cinnamon mixture.', 'Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes, or until bread is lightly browned.']

title: Pork chops with caramelized onions

title: Sausage and peppers
recipe: ['Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.', 'Add sausage; cook and stir 5 min.', 'Or until evenly browned.', 'Add peppers and onions; cook and stir 5 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender.', 'Stir in tomatoes; cook 5 min.', 'Or until heated through, stirring occasionally.']

title: Sauteed spinach with carrots

title: Roasted potatoes with garlic and parsley

title: Citrus punch
recipe: ['Combine all ingredients in a large punch bowl.', 'Serve over ice.']

title: Breakfast banana split

title: Berry salad
recipe: ['Toss berries with dressing.', 'Top with sunflower kernels.']

title: Grilled cheese sandwich
recipe: ['Fill bread slices with singles and tomatoes to make 2 sandwiches.', 'Spread outsides of sandwiches with butter.', 'Cook in skillet on medium heat 3 min.', 'On each side or until golden brown on both sides.']

title: Spinach and tomato frittata
recipe: ['Heat oven to 350f.', 'Cook and stir onions and garlic in large nonstick skillet on medium heat 5 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender.', 'Add spinach; cook and stir 2 min.', 'Or just until wilted.', 'Whisk eggs and pepper in medium bowl until blended.', 'Add to spinach mixture; mix well.', 'Pour into 9-inch pie plate sprayed with cooking spray.', 'Bake 25 min.', 'Or until center is set.', 'Top with cheese; bake 5 min.', 'Or until melted.']

title: Salmon with roasted red pepper and olive oil
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 400.2.', 'Combine bell pepper, olive oil, and salt in a large bowl; toss to coat.', 'Arrange bell pepper mixture on a jelly-roll pan.', 'Bake at 400 for 10 minutes or until blackened.', 'Place bell pepper mixture in a zip-top plastic bag; seal.', 'Let stand 10 minutes.', 'Peel and discard skin.', 'Cut bell pepper into 8 wedges.', 'Place bell pepper wedges on a jelly-roll pan; drizzle with 1 tablespoon oil.', 'Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon salt.', 'Bake at 400 for 10 minutes or until blackened.', 'Place bell pepper wedges on a jelly-roll pan; broil 5 minutes or until blackened.', 'Place bell pepper wedges in a zip-top plastic bag; seal']

title: Grilled burgers
recipe: ['In a large bowl, combine the ground beef, onion, salt, pepper and 1 cup of the cheese.', 'Shape into 4 patties.', 'Heat a grill pan over medium-high heat.', 'Brush the patties with oil.', 'Grill the patties for 5 minutes on each side, or until done.', 'Top each patty with a slice of tomato and lettuce.']

title: Balsamic roasted green beans
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 450f.', 'Toss green beans with oil, rosemary, and pepper in large bowl.', 'Spread in single layer on large baking sheet.', 'Bake 10 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender, stirring after 5 min.', 'Stir in vinegar.']

title: Homemade pancake mix
recipe: ['In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, and salt.', 'In a separate bowl, whisk together the milk, eggs, and vanilla.', 'Pour the milk mixture into the flour mixture and stir until smooth.', 'Heat a large skillet over medium heat.', 'Pour in the butter and swirl to coat the bottom of the pan.', 'Pour in the batter and cook until the edges are dry and the center is set, about 2 minutes.', 'Flip and cook until golden brown, about 2 minutes more.']

title: Brussels sprouts with garlic and lemon

title: Baked eggs
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f.', 'In a large bowl, combine eggs, milk, salt, and pepper.', 'Add the melted butter and mix well.', 'Pour into a greased 9x13 baking dish.', 'Bake for 30 minutes.']

title: Stir-fried broccoli and peppers
recipe: ['Heat oil in large nonstick skillet on medium-high heat.', 'Add broccoli, peppers and onions; stir-fry 5 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender.', 'Add garlic; stir-fry 1 min.', 'Add soy sauce and ginger; stir-fry 1 min.', 'Add cornstarch; stir-fry 1 min.', 'Or until sauce is thickened and vegetables are crisp-tender.', 'Serve over rice.']

title: Pasta with mushrooms and peas

title: Pesto
recipe: ['Place all ingredients in food processor or blender.', 'Process until smooth.']

title: Broccoli cheddar soup
recipe: ['In a large saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.', 'Add onion and cook until tender.', 'Stir in flour and cook for 1 minute.', 'Gradually stir in chicken broth and milk.', 'Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.', 'Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.', 'Stir in broccoli, carrots, salt and pepper.', 'Cook for 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.', 'Stir in cheese until melted.']

title: Chocolate chunk cookies
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f.', 'In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.', 'Add egg and vanilla and beat until combined.', 'In a separate bowl, combine flour, salt and chocolate.', 'Add to the creamed mixture and mix until combined.', 'Roll dough into 1-inch balls and place on a parchment lined baking sheet.', 'Bake for 10-12 minutes or until lightly browned.', 'Remove from oven and let cool on the baking sheet for a few minutes before removing to a wire rack to cool completely.']

title: Roasted broccoli with garlic
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 425 degrees f. line a baking sheet with parchment paper.', 'In a large bowl, toss broccoli with olive oil, garlic, salt and pepper.', 'Spread broccoli on baking sheet in a single layer.', 'Roast for 15 minutes, tossing halfway through.']

title: Broccoli rabe with garlic and olive oil

title: Rice with mushrooms and peas
recipe: ['Heat oil in large nonstick skillet on medium-high heat.', 'Add mushrooms and onions; cook and stir 5 min.', 'Or until tender.', 'Stir in water, soy sauce and rice; bring to boil.', 'Cover; simmer on medium-low heat 5 min.', 'Remove from heat.', 'Let stand, covered, 5 min.', 'Fluff with fork.']

title: Grilled salmon with cilantro and lime
recipe: ['In a small bowl, combine the cilantro, garlic, onion, lime juice, olive oil, salt and pepper.', 'Set aside.', 'Preheat a grill pan over medium-high heat.', 'Brush the salmon fillets with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.', 'Grill the salmon for about 4 minutes per side, or until the fish flakes easily with a fork.', 'Serve the salmon topped with the cilantro mixture.']

title: Kraft hickory bbq steak
recipe: ['Heat grill to medium heat.', 'Grill steak 8 to 10 min.', 'On each side or until medium doneness (160f), brushing occasionally with barbecue sauce.', 'Cut steak across the grain into thin slices.', 'Serve with the steak.']

title: Cinnamon roll
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 400 degrees f (200 degrees c).', 'Grease a 10x15 inch jellyroll pan.', 'In a large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.', 'Beat in the eggs one at a time, then stir in the flour, salt and cinnamon.', 'Spread the dough evenly into the prepared pan.', 'Bake for 15 minutes in the preheated oven, until lightly browned.', 'Remove from oven and spread the cinnamon sugar over the hot crust.', 'Roll the dough out to a 10x15 inch rectangle.', 'Cut into strips and place strips over the cinnamon sugar.', 'Bake for 15 minutes in the preheated oven, or until golden brown.']

title: Avocado and feta rice salad
recipe: ['Mix all ingredients except dressing in large bowl.', 'Add dressing; mix lightly.']

title: Marshmallow sundae sauce

title: Easy grilled pork chops

title: Chocolate chess pie
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f (175 degrees c).', 'In a large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.', 'Beat in the eggs one at a time, then stir in the vanilla.', 'Combine the cream, milk, and salt; stir into the sugar mixture.', 'Pour filling into the pie shell.', 'Bake in the preheated oven for 50 minutes, or until a knife inserted into the center comes out clean.', 'Cool on a wire rack.']

title: Snickerdoodle cookies

title: Cheesy potato bake

title: Brussels sprouts with bacon and tomatoes

title: Stuffed acorn squash

title: Chicken fajitas
recipe: ['Heat large nonstick skillet on medium-high heat.', 'Add chicken; cook and stir 5 min.', 'Or until done.', 'Stir in peppers and onions; cook 5 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.', 'Stir in cilantro.', 'Spoon chicken mixture down centers of tortillas; roll up.']

title: Grilled pita chips
recipe: ['Preheat grill to medium-high heat.2.', 'Combine oil, lemon juice, salt, and pepper in a large bowl; stir well.', 'Add bread; toss to coat.', 'Arrange pita wedges on a grill rack coated with cooking spray; grill 2 minutes on each side or until lightly browned.', 'Serve with the dressing.']

title: Bread machine doughnuts
recipe: ['Add all ingredients to bread machine in the order recommended by the manufacturer.', 'Select dough cycle; press start.', 'When cycle is complete, remove dough from machine and shape into a ball.', 'Place on a lightly floured surface and let rest for 10 minutes.', 'Roll out dough to 1/4 inch thickness.', 'Cut into desired shapes with a floured doughnut cutter.', 'Place on greased baking sheets.', 'Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in size, about 30 minutes.', 'Bake at 350 degrees f (175 degrees c) for 10 to 12 minutes.']

title: Peach and apple crisp
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 375 degrees f.', 'In a large bowl, toss together the apples, peaches, sugar, cinnamon, and salt.', 'Transfer to a greased 8-inch square baking dish.', 'In a small bowl, combine the flour, brown sugar, and butter.', 'Using a pastry cutter or two forks, cut the butter into the flour mixture until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.', 'Sprinkle the crumb mixture over the fruit.', 'Bake for 30 minutes or until the topping is golden brown.', 'Serve warm with ice cream.']

title: Grilled chicken wings

title: Grilled salmon with garlic and soy sauce

title: Sparkling citrus spritzer
recipe: ['Add water to drink mix in large plastic or glass pitcher; stir until mix is dissolved.', 'Stir in club soda.', 'Serve over ice.']

title: Grilled salmon with asparagus and lemon

title: Roasted tomato and onion relish

recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350f.', 'Cut squash in half lengthwise; remove seeds.', 'Place squash halves, cut sides up, on baking sheet.', 'Bake 30 minutes or until tender.', 'Melt butter in large skillet on medium heat.', 'Add squash; cook and stir 5 minutes or until lightly browned.', 'Add velveeta; cook until velveeta is completely melted and mixture is well blended, stirring frequently.', 'Spoon into serving bowl; sprinkle with salt and pepper.']

title: Pasta with caramelized onions and garlic
recipe: ['In a large skillet, heat the olive oil over medium heat.', 'Add the onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until they are golden brown, about 15 minutes.', 'Add the garlic and cook, stirring, until fragrant, about 30 seconds.', 'Add the butter and cook, stirring, until the butter melts, about 1 minute.', 'Add the salt and pepper and cook, stirring, until the onions are golden brown, about 5 minutes.', 'Add the pasta and cook, stirring, until the pasta is al dente, about 5 minutes.', 'Add the parmesan and toss to coat.', 'Serve immediately.']

title: Roasted red pepper and manchego cheese crostini
recipe: ['Heat oven to 400 degrees f.', 'Place baguette slices on baking sheet; brush with oil.', 'Bake 8 to 10 min.', 'Or until lightly toasted, turning after 4 min.', 'Spread toast slices with cream cheese product; top with peppers and manchego.']

title: Roasted butternut squash & red pepper salad
recipe: ['Heat oven to 400 degrees f.', 'Toss squash with oil and pepper; spread onto parchment-covered rimmed baking sheet.', 'Bake 40 min.', 'Or until squash is tender and golden brown, stirring after 15 min.', 'Cool.', 'Combine vegetables and dressing in large bowl.', 'Add cheese; mix lightly.']

title: Cinnamon cheesecake
recipe: ['Heat oven to 350f.', 'Mix cream cheese, butter and sugar until blended.', 'Add eggs; mix just until blended.', 'Pour into crust.', 'Bake 40 min.', 'Or until centre is almost set.', 'Cool.', 'Refrigerate 3 hours.', 'Top with apples just before serving.']

title: Oatmeal cookies
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f.', 'In a large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.', 'Beat in the egg and vanilla.', 'Combine the flour, baking powder and salt; stir into the creamed mixture.', 'Stir in oats.', 'Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.', 'Bake for 10-12 minutes or until lightly browned.', 'Cool on wire racks.']

title: Parmesan pesto
recipe: ['Place all ingredients in a food processor and pulse until smooth.', 'Serve immediately.']

title: Fried onion rings
recipe: ['Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.', 'Add onion and garlic; cook and stir until onion is tender, about 5 minutes.', 'Add salt and pepper to taste.', 'Remove from heat and set aside.', 'Beat eggs in a shallow dish.', 'Dip onion rings in egg mixture, then in bread crumbs.', 'Fry in hot oil until golden brown, about 3 minutes per side.']

title: Cranberry relish
recipe: ['In a medium saucepan, combine the cranberries, sugar, orange zest and juice and bring to a boil.', 'Cook over moderately high heat, stirring occasionally, until the cranberries burst, about 10 minutes.', 'Let cool completely.', 'Transfer the relish to a bowl and refrigerate until chilled, about 1 hour.']

title: Creamy cinnamon cream cheese sauce
recipe: ['Mix cream cheese, butter and sugar in medium bowl until blended.', 'Stir in milk.']

title: Cinnamon streusel muffins
recipe: ['Heat oven to 400 degrees f.', 'Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in large bowl.', 'Cut in butter with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.', 'Stir in cereal.', 'Whisk egg and milk in small bowl until blended.', 'Add to flour mixture; stir just until moistened.', '(batter will be lumpy.)', 'Spoon into 12 muffin pan cups sprayed with cooking spray.', 'Mix brown sugar and cinnamon in small bowl.', 'Sprinkle over batter.', 'Bake 20 to 25 min.', 'Or until toothpick inserted in centres comes out clean.', 'Cool in pan 5 min.', 'Remove to wire rack; cool completely.']

title: Salade de terre avec legumes rotis
recipe: ['Place the potatoes in a large pot and cover with water.', 'Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until the potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes.', 'Drain and allow to cool.', 'Place the potatoes in a large bowl and add the carrots, apples, and cucumbers.', 'Season with salt and pepper.', 'Toss to combine.', 'Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.']

title: Spinach and mushroom cannelloni
recipe: ['Heat oven to 350f.', 'Cook and stir onions and garlic in hot oil in large skillet on medium heat 5 min.', 'Or until onions are crisp-tender.', 'Add mushrooms; cook and stir 5 min.', 'Or until mushrooms are tender.', 'Stir in spinach; cook and stir 2 min.', 'Or just until wilted.', 'Remove from heat.', 'Stir in ricotta and pepper.', 'Spoon into manicotti shells; place in 13x9-inch baking dish sprayed with cooking spray.', 'Cover with sauce.', 'Bake 20 min.', 'Or until heated through.', 'Sprinkle with parmesan.']

title: Beet juice
recipe: ['Wash beets and cut into chunks.', 'Place in a large pot with water and sugar.', 'Bring to a boil and cook until tender.', 'Remove from heat and let cool.', 'Add lemon juice and stir.', 'Serve.']

title: Cranberry orange relish
recipe: ['Combine all ingredients in medium bowl.', 'Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.']

title: Roasted red pepper and onion relish
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 400 degrees f (200 degrees c).', 'Place red bell pepper, onion, and garlic on a baking sheet.', 'Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.', 'Roast in the preheated oven until vegetables are tender and lightly browned, about 30 minutes.']

title: Libbie's sweet onion casserole
recipe: ['Mix together the onion, salt, pepper, sugar, and butter.', 'Add the milk and eggs.', 'Mix well.', 'Pour into a greased casserole dish.', 'Bake at 350 degrees fahrenheit for 1 hour.']

title: Grilled chicken breasts with creamy tomato sauce
recipe: ['Heat grill to medium heat.', 'Grill chicken 6 to 8 min.', 'On each side or until done (165f).', 'Meanwhile, mix dressing and cheese.', 'Serve chicken topped with tomato sauce mixture.']

title: Cinnamon sugar cookies
recipe: ['Heat oven to 350f.', 'Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt in bowl.', 'Beat butter and milk in large bowl with mixer until light and fluffy.', 'Add egg; mix well.', 'Gradually add flour mixture, beating well after each addition.', 'Shape dough into 1-inch balls.', 'Place, 2 inches apart, on baking sheets.', 'Flatten each ball slightly with bottom of drinking glass.', 'Bake 10 to 12 min.', 'Or until lightly browned.', 'Cool on baking sheets 1 min.', 'Remove to wire racks; cool completely.']

title: Apple crisp
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees.', 'In a large bowl, combine the apples, sugar, cinnamon, and salt.', 'Pour into a greased 8-inch square baking dish.', 'In a small bowl, combine the flour, oats, brown sugar, baking powder and butter.', 'Cut in the butter until crumbly.', 'Sprinkle over the apples.', 'Bake for 35-40 minutes or until apples are tender.']

title: Cream cheese cupcakes
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. line a 12-count muffin tin with paper liners.', 'In a large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.', 'Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.', 'Add the vanilla and beat until combined.', 'In a separate bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.', 'Add the dry ingredients to the creamed mixture and mix until just combined.', 'Fill the muffin liners 2/3 full.', 'Bake for 18-20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.', 'Remove from the oven and allow to cool completely.', 'In a small bowl, combine the cream cheese, butter and vanilla until smooth.', 'Add the powdered']

title: Cinnamon coffee cake
recipe: ['Heat oven to 350f.', 'Combine flour, baking powder and salt in bowl.', 'Beat butter and sugar in large bowl with mixer until light and fluffy.', 'Blend in eggs and vanilla.', 'Gradually beat in flour mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.', 'Pour into greased 13x9-inch baking pan.', 'Bake 40 to 45 min.', 'Or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.', 'Cool completely.', 'Combine all glaze ingredients in bowl.', 'Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed.', 'Drizzle over cake.']

title: Chocolate peanut butter cups
recipe: ['Microwave chocolate and peanut butter in large microwaveable bowl on high 2 min.', 'Or until butter is melted; stir until chocolate is completely melted.', 'Stir in cream cheese.', 'Spoon into 12 paper-lined muffin cups.', 'Refrigerate 1 hour or until firm.']

title: Chocolate truffle cheesecake
recipe: ['Heat oven to 350f.', 'Beat cream cheese, butter and sugar in large bowl with mixer until blended.', 'Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing on low speed after each just until blended.', 'Stir in chocolate.', 'Pour into 9-inch springform pan sprayed with cooking spray.', 'Bake 40 min.', 'Or until centre is almost set.', 'Run knife around rim of pan to loosen cake; cool before removing rim.', 'Refrigerate cheesecake 4 hours.', 'Microwave chocolate and milk in microwaveable bowl on high 1 min.', '; stir until chocolate is completely melted and mixture is well blended.', 'Cool 10 min.', '; pour over cheesecake.', 'Refrigerate 3 hours.']

title: Butterscotch bundt cake
recipe: ['Heat oven to 350f.', 'Beat first 5 ingredients in large bowl with mixer until blended.', 'Stir in nuts.', 'Pour into greased and floured 12-cup fluted tube pan or 10-inch tube pan.', 'Bake 50 to 55 min.', 'Or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.', 'Cool cake in pan 10 min.', 'Loosen cake from sides of pan with knife.', 'Invert cake onto wire rack; gently remove pan.', 'Cool cake completely.', 'Mix sugar and cinnamon until blended; drizzle over cake.']

title: Cheesecake
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 325f.', 'Mix graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar.', 'Press firmly onto bottom of 9-inch springform pan.', 'Bake 10 minutes.', 'Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.', 'Add sour cream and flour; mix well.', 'Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing on low speed after each addition just until blended.', 'Pour over crust.', 'Bake 1 hour 10 minutes.', 'Run knife around rim of pan to loosen cake; cool before removing rim.', 'Refrigerate 4 hours.']

title: Cheesy frittata
recipe: ['Heat oven to 350f.', 'Whisk eggs and milk in medium bowl until blended.', 'Add remaining ingredients; mix well.', 'Pour into 9-inch pie plate sprayed with cooking spray.', 'Bake 40 min.', 'Or until center is set.']

title: Pecan pie
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350f.', 'Beat eggs in large bowl with wire whisk until foamy.', 'Add sugar, corn syrup and butter; mix well.', 'Stir in pecans and 1/2 cup of the almonds.', 'Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.', 'Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until center is set.', 'Cool completely.', 'Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup almonds.', 'Store leftover pie in refrigerator.']

title: Spaghetti with mushrooms and onions
recipe: ['Cook spaghetti in large pot of boiling salted water until just tender but still firm to bite, stirring occasionally.', 'Drain.', 'Meanwhile, heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.', 'Add mushrooms and onions; saute until tender, about 5 minutes.', 'Add garlic and saute until fragrant, about 1 minute.', 'Add spaghetti and toss to coat.', 'Add parsley, salt and pepper; toss to combine.', 'Sprinkle with cheese.']

title: Mushroom risotto
recipe: ['Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.', 'Add mushrooms and onion; cook and stir until tender.', 'Stir in rice and cook until heated through.', 'Add butter and stir until melted.', 'Season with salt and pepper.']

title: Vanilla shortbread cookies
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f.', 'In a large bowl, cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.', 'Add vanilla and salt and mix well.', 'Add flour and mix until just combined.', 'Roll dough into 1-inch balls and place on a parchment lined baking sheet.', 'Bake for 10-12 minutes or until just starting to brown around the edges.', 'Remove from oven and let cool on a wire rack.']

title: Almond rice pudding
recipe: ['Bring water to a boil in a medium saucepan.', 'Stir in rice and salt.', 'Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer 20 minutes.', 'Stir in almond milk and cook 5 minutes more.']

title: Korean bulgogi
recipe: ['Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.', 'Add beef and toss to coat.', 'Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.', 'Preheat grill to medium-high heat.', 'Remove beef from marinade and discard marinade.', 'Grill beef for 5 minutes per side, or until desired doneness.']

title: Avocado crema
recipe: ['Combine all ingredients in a blender and puree until smooth.', 'Serve immediately.']

title: Balsamic spa salad
recipe: ['Toss greens with mangos, avocados and peppers in large bowl.', 'Add dressing; mix lightly.']

title: Cream cheese swirl bars
recipe: ['Heat oven to 350f.', 'Combine flour, baking soda and salt.', 'Beat butter, oil and sugar in large bowl with mixer until light and fluffy.', 'Blend in eggs and vanilla.', 'Gradually beat in flour mixture.', 'Stir in nuts.', 'Spread into greased 13x9-inch baking pan.', 'Bake 25 to 30 min.', 'Or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.', 'Cool completely.', 'Beat cream cheese, butter and vanilla in large bowl with mixer until blended.', 'Gradually beat in powdered sugar.', 'Spread over bars.']

title: Cinnamon swirl cake
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. grease and flour a 9 x 13 pan.', 'In a large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.', 'Set aside.', 'In a large bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.', 'Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.', 'Add vanilla and beat until combined.', 'Add flour mixture and beat until just combined.', 'Pour batter into prepared pan.', 'In a small bowl, combine brown sugar and cinnamon.', 'Sprinkle over batter.', 'Bake for 35-40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.', 'Cool in pan for 10 minutes.', 'Remove from pan and cool completely on a wire rack.']

title: Asian broccoli slaw
recipe: ['Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.', 'Add broccoli and carrots; toss to coat.', 'Sprinkle with green onions.']

title: Butternut squash soup
recipe: ['Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.', 'Add onion and garlic; cook 5 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.', 'Add squash, broth, salt, and pepper; bring to a boil.', 'Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 20 minutes or until squash is tender.', 'Remove from heat; cool slightly.', 'Working in batches, puree soup in a blender or food processor until smooth.', 'Return soup to pan; stir in cream.', 'Heat through.']

title: Potato latkes
recipe: ['Grate potatoes and onion.', 'Squeeze out excess liquid.', 'Combine potatoes, onion, garlic, egg, salt and pepper in large bowl.', 'Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.', 'Drop potato mixture by 1/4 cupfuls into skillet, flattening slightly with back of spoon.', 'Cook 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until golden brown.', 'Drain on paper towels.', 'Serve with sour cream, if desired.']

title: Roasted carrots with peppers
recipe: ['Heat oven to 425 degrees f.', 'Toss carrots with oil; spread onto rimmed baking sheet.', 'Bake 25 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender, stirring after 15 min.', 'Sprinkle with pepper.']

title: Spring vegetable stir-fry
recipe: ['Heat oil in large nonstick skillet on medium-high heat.', 'Add vegetables; stir-fry 5 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender.', 'Add beans and dressing; stir-fry 2 min.', 'Or until heated through.', 'Serve over rice.']

title: Strawberry lemonade
recipe: ['In a large pitcher, combine the strawberries, lemon juice, sugar and water.', 'Stir until sugar is dissolved.', 'Chill until cold.']
